[chapter:"V3 Feature Showcase"]
Welcome to the zen-board v3 roadmap demo. Today we're showcasing the new slideshow and overlay primitives.
[slide:pyramids:center:pop]
The new [slide:pyramids:fullscreen:fade] primitive lets you drop images instantly without the hand-drawn reveal.
[lower3rd:"Slide Primitive":"Instant image drop with transitions"]
That's perfect for meme-talking style videos.
[slide:city:TR:fade]
[arrow:TL:BR:curved:0.5] Notice how this curved arrow draws attention to the hero image.
[highlight:100,200,400,150:pulse:2.0]
The [highlight:] primitive creates attention boxes with animated marching ants or pulsing rings.
[compare:robot:world:"Code World":"Real World":"Before"]
Lower thirds slide in and out automatically: [lower3rd:"Lower Third Demo":"Animated name card":4.0:FF4444]
[wait:1.0]
[transition:fade-black:0.5]
Transitions enable scene segmentation between topics.
[slide:city:LH:slide-left]
Slides can use seven transition types: none, fade, pop, slide-left, slide-right, slide-up, slide-down.
[overlay:world:0.3:fullscreen]
Persistent semi-transparent overlays (watermarks, vignettes) stay on until explicitly erased.
[erase:*]
Wipe the board clean and start fresh.
[clear]
The v3 renderer now supports embedded Go fonts — no Linux font paths required.
[style:blackboard]
Switching to [style:blackboard] dark board mode with automatic color inversion.
[lower3rd:"Blackboard Mode":"Automatic inverted colors"]
[slide:pyramids:center:slide-up]
Blackboard style inverts asset colors for contrast.
And that wraps the v3 feature preview.
[style:whiteboard]
[chapter:"End"]
Thanks for watching.
